{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Particle Text",
  "description": "Particle Text — text baked into FluidSim2D's force field as a curl-rotated gradient. Same atom-decomposed base as FluidSim2D (`seed_particles` + wgsl_compute pattern + `cast_as_particle` + `array_feedback` particle loop + per-particle `sample / anti_clump / euler / wrap / apply_radial_burst` integrator + texture-domain `gradient_central_diff / scale_offset / rotate_vec2_by_angle` force field with `simplex_field_2d`-based density-adaptive noise advection), with one extra branch grafted in.\n\nText-force branch added in parallel to the velocity field: `node.render_text → gaussian_blur H+V (softens the gradient so it isn't single-texel spiky) → gradient_central_diff (R channel, texel-scale, clamp wrap) → rotate_vec2_by_angle (angle=PI/2: perpendicular curl-along-edge flow, divergence-free) → gain (driven by outer-card text_strength)`. That contribution is summed into the existing field + noise combiner via `mix(Add)` so the per-particle sampler reads field + noise + text in one composed texture.\n\nOuter-card params on top of the FluidSim2D surface: `text` (string), `fontFamily` (string), `text_size` (font height as a fraction of output height, 0.05..1.0, default 0.25), `text_strength` (gain on the text-derived force, 0..20, default 4.0).\n\nDeparture from legacy ParticleText visual: particles never \"form the text and dissolve\" — the text is a persistent attractor / repeller depending on local flow direction. Best results with text_strength 3-8 and text_size 0.3-0.6 against FluidSim2D defaults. Increase `feather` for chunkier glyph trails; increase `count_m` to fill the text shape more densely.",
